The method below is intended to count how many times the single-character String `target` appears in String `s`. Which of the following correctly identifies the bug?

```java
public static int countChar(String s, String target) {
    int count = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i <= s.length(); i++) {
        if (s.substring(i, i + 1).equals(target)) {
            count++;
        }
    }
    return count;
}
```

